      <div class="msgContentFrame">You can see how many SP you need to move up a rank on your Lodestone profile.  I'm sure I'm not the only one hoping that at some point SE will add the ability to see your Sentinel SP/TNR in-game, but for now Lodestone is your only option. <br /> <br />It does go up in ranks, and it requires the same amount of SP to do so as any other class, but it takes longer than other classes to rank up because you rarely got as much or more shield skill as you do sword.  I've been using a shield while ranking up gladiator, thaumaturge, and conjurer.  All three classes can earn shield skill points with a shield equipped and guard up.  Gladiator is rank 17, thaumaturge is 18, and conjurer is 16.  Three classes earning shield skill with ranks in the high teens.  My sentinel rank is 14. <br /> <br />Apparently a lot of tanks are putting no merit in sentinel rank at all, preferring to focus on sword skill for gladiator ranks.  Can't say I fully support that notion, but even after SE adjusts the SP requirements to rank any class from 1-20, sentinel is going to be a long, long haul to the cap.</div>
